Hawaii Auto Shipping 


 

Hawaii Auto Shipping with us feels like a Vacation
Coastal Auto Shipping is one of the leading provider of Hawaii Services to ship a car to and from the Islands. Including services from the Ports of Honolulu, Hilo, Kahului, Kona and Nawiliwili. We are the expert choice and proud to offer customers easy and affordable transport services. Hawaii Auto Shipping may sound difficult to the point of selling your vehicle. At time making customers not consider the option of possibly shipping the vehicle. But with Coastal Auto Shipping that decision can change. Offering valuable knowledge on your ocean move to Hawaii. We can tailor a service that will fit your needs providing free instant auto transport quotes. Accommodating any schedule desired for you. While adjusting to transit times which will vary depending on origin. With frequent sailings from each of the major ports. We offer weekly and bi-weekly services, with direct sailing from Long Beach, CA to Honolulu, HI every week. We also extend our car hauling services to our military troops on Permanent Change of Station. We’re partnered with names you know and trust such as Matson Navigation and PASHA. You can rely on a team of specialists which simplifies the entire auto transportation process.






Port Location






Auto shipping to Hawaii






Auto shipping from Hawaii






Hawaii Vehicle Tracking









 

AUTO SHIPPING SERVICES TO AND FROM HAWAII:







									Port to Port Service								
Port to Port Service

When transporting a car to Hawaii from the mainland U.S and headed to one of the connecting islands which include The Big Island, Oahu, Maui and Kaua’i. You will take your own personal vehicle to the port of either Seattle, Oakland or Long Beach and pick up the vehicle at the final destination in Hawaii. If leaving one of the Islands of Hawaii and headed back to the mainland, ports will include Honolulu, Hilo, Kahului and the Nawiliwili Harbor. Transit times will vary depending on the port of origin.







									Port to Door Service								
Port to Door Service

Auto shipping from Hawaii to the mainland is now easier than ever. You will take your vehicle to either to the Honolulu, Hilo, Kahului or Nawiliwili Port. After the vehicle is loaded in the belly of the ship (Not Exposed To Elements). The vessel departs to the mainland ports Seattle, Oakland or Long Beach. Once the vessel arrives in the mainland port destined to we assign a transporter for pick up. The transport will pick up your vehicle on a Multiple Car Carrier from the port and take the vehicle to a destination provided when the order was processed. Transit times will vary depending on the destination for delivery. Look Below for Rules and Regulations.







									Door to Port Service								
Door to Port Service

Auto shipping to Hawaii from the mainland is now easier than ever. We come to the address provided by you when the order was processed. The vehicle will be loaded on a Car Carrier and transported to the port of departure on the West Coast. It can either be Seattle, Oakland or Long Beach depending on pick up origin. After the vehicle is loaded in the belly of the ship (Not Exposed To Elements). Vehicle must be picked up by the contact provided in the port of destination. Which can either be Honolulu, Hilo, Kahului or the Nawiliwili Harbor. Transit times will vary depending on origin of pick up. Proper identification must provided when picking up the vehicle.







									Rules and Regulations								
Rules and Regulations

When leaving the Islands of Hawaii or Eastbound Shipments Only the following will be required:

Copy of the title or Ownership Document of the vehicle
If the vehicle is still under a Lien you will need what’s called a Lien Holders Authorization Form. It’s basically a permission letter from the bank or dealership letting you ship the vehicle and will be provided by your current title holder
Proof of Valid Registration and Insurance (If the vehicle is not registered please contact your local Hawaii DMV )
A picture ID or identification card
A booking reservation number provided by our company to you








									Vehicle Preparation								
Vehicle Preparation


Automobile must be cleaned inside and out
No personal belongings inside the vehicle (Only items allowed are the documents kept in the glove box and one baby seat)
The fuel or gas tank must contain 1/4 or less
Chips or cracks on the windshield have to be repaired
The emergency brake has to be in proper working order








									Payment Methods								
Payment Methods


