In Focus

Increased West Coast – South Pacific Service
Matson’s “South Pacific Express” (SPX) links the company’s well established West Coast – Hawaii service with its South Pacific network, using a dedicated ship to carry West Coast cargo transshipped at Honolulu. Starting May 30, 2017, Matson will increase the frequency of its SPX service to Samoa and American Samoa from 28 days to 14 days. For a complete list of port calls and schedule information,click here


